🚀 TaskResult validate() kya karta hai?
👉 validate() check karta hai ki object valid state me hai ya nahi
👉 Agar koi problem hai → error throw karega
💡 Simple Definition:-
👉 validate() = “object sahi hai ya nahi check karo”
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 validate() kya-kya check karta hai?
1️⃣ Required Fields Check:-
👉 Important fields null na ho

result.setName(null);
result.validate(); // ❌ error

Output:-
Validation Error: name is required

2️⃣ Status Valid hai ya nahi:-
👉 Invalid status allow nahi

result.setStatus("XYZ");
result.validate();

Output:-
Validation Error: invalid status

3️⃣ Time Consistency Check:-
👉 Start time < End time hona chahiye

result.setStartTime(new Date(2000));
result.setEndTime(new Date(1000));
result.validate();

Output:-
Validation Error: endTime before startTime

4️⃣ Completion Logic Check:-
👉 Completed hai to end time hona chahiye

result.setStatus("Completed");
result.setEndTime(null);
result.validate();

Output:-
Validation Error: endTime required for completed task

5️⃣ Progress Range Check:-
👉 0–100 ke beech hona chahiye

result.setPercentComplete(150);
result.validate();

Output:-
Validation Error: percent out of range

6️⃣ Retry Logic Check:-
👉 retryCount <= maxRetries

result.setRetryCount(5);
result.setMaxRetries(3);
result.validate();

Output:-
Validation Error: retry exceeded

7️⃣ Attributes / Arguments Format Check:-
👉 Map sahi format me ho

result.setAttributes(null);
result.validate();

Output:-
Validation Error: attributes invalid.
